WLC_RUN(3)                                               WLC CORE API FUNCTIONS

NAME

    wlc_run - run the main event loop

SYNOPSIS

    void wlc_run(void);

DESCRIPTION

    wlc_run() starts the main event loop for the interface initialized by 
    wlc_init().  wlc_run() should be called after setup routines and
    wlc_init().

RETURN VALUE

    None.

NOTES

    If wlc_run() is called before wlc_init() then nothing shall happen.

    If wlc_run() is called more than once after wlc_init() then only the first
    call will have effect.

ALSO SEE
    
    wlc_init(3), wlc_terminate(3)
